&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planned Interview Date: 27th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want our hospitals to be great places to work, that are truly inclusive and responsive to staff voice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This varied and interesting role will support our improvement journey, specifically around equality, diversity, inclusion, and staff engagement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are educated to degree level or equivalent and have experience working in the equality, diversity, and inclusion field we would love to hear from you. We are also looking for evidence of continuous professional development and excellent interpersonal and presentation skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All new staff appointed to posts at the Trust are subject to a probationary period. This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the culture and working environment of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications should be made online, however, queries regarding the application process or assistance with the completion of the form (for applicants with a disability) can be made to Amanda Vickers, HR Recruitment Department, on 01708 435000 ext 3861. Further details regarding the post may be obtained by contacting the manager as per the contact details below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire O&#39;TooleJob titleHead of InclusionEmail addressclaire.o&#39;toole@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
